'''Beatrice Richter''' (born 20 December 1948 in [[Munich]]) is a German TV actress, [[comedian]], [[cabaret]] artist and jazz singer.

Beatrice Richter concluded an acting education at the [[Otto Falckenberg School of the Performing Arts]] in Munich, which was followed by a jazz dance training under Frank Hatchett in New York.<ref name="TA">{{cite web |url=http://www.trusted-agents.de/no_cache/schauspielerinnen/person/beatrice-richter/detail.html |title=Beatrice Richter |website=trusted-agents.de  |language= de|accessdate=2014-11-17}}</ref>

She began her career with [[Diether Krebs]] and [[Klaus Havenstein]] at the side of [[Rudi Carrell]] in the [[Radio Bremen]] comedy program ''{{Interlanguage link multi|Rudis Tagesshow|de}}'', which ran from 1981 till 1987. For her [[parody]] performances she was awarded the [[Goldene Kamera]] in 1982.<ref name="TA" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldenekamera.de/de/chronik1980/1980/1989/1982 |title=Die Goldene Kamera 1982 – 11. Februar 1982 |date= |website=goldenekamera.de |publisher=[[Hörzu]] |language=de |accessdate=2014-11-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129183107/http://www.goldenekamera.de/de/chronik1980/1980/1989/1982 |archivedate=2014-11-29 |df= }}</ref> She gained further recognition as partner of Diether Krebs in the sketch comedy serial ''{{Interlanguage link multi|Sketchup (Comedy)|de|3=Sketchup (Comedy)|lt=Sketchup}}'' ([[Bayerischer Rundfunk]], 1984–1986), her role was later taken over by [[Iris Berben]]. Beatrice Richter furthermore starred in several films with among others [[Walter Giller]] and [[Peter Alexander (Austrian performer)|Peter Alexander]] and also appeared in theater [[Play (theatre)|plays]].<ref name="TA" /> In 1989 she was seen in the episode “Hilfe eine Aushilfe!” (“Help a temp!”) of the television series ''[[Meister Eder und sein Pumuckl (TV series)|Meister Eder und sein Pumuckl]]''. Since 1996 she entertained, also as a singer, in her own jazz cabaret show.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.stern.de/lifestyle/leute/was-macht-eigentlich-beatrice-richter-72422.html |title=Was macht eigentlich: Beatrice Richter|last1=Röbke |first1=Thomas |last2=Richter |first2=Beatrice |date=2001-06-15 |website=stern.de |publisher=[[Stern (magazine)|Stern]] |language= de|accessdate=2014-11-17}}</ref>

In 2004 she appeared on stage with Peter Schmidt-Pavloff, [[Johannes Heesters]], [[Cordula Trantow]] and Fred Alexander in [[Hugo von Hofmannsthal]]'s play [[Jedermann (play)|Jedermann]] in front of the [[Cologne Cathedral]]. There she played the roles of the ''Journeyman'', the ''Devil'' and the ''Mammon''.<ref name="WWW" />
In 2008 she played the role of ''Rosmathilda Polterman'' at the [[Karl May Festival in Bad Segeberg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=umWYlnF2p5U |title=Rosmatilda Polterman |date=2008-09-09 |website=youtube.com |publisher= |accessdate=2014-11-17}}</ref><ref name="VKST">{{cite web |url=http://www.smago.de/d/artikel/53224/ |title=Beatrice Richter mit Tochter Judith Mittwochmorgen (27.04.2011) in 'Volle Kanne – Service täglich' zu Gast! |date=2011-04-26 |website=smago.de |language= de|accessdate=2014-11-17}}</ref>

Photos of her appeared in the August 1982 edition of the German [[Playboy]] magazine.<ref name="WWW">{{cite web |url=http://www.was-war-wann.de/personen/beatrice_richter.html |title=Biografie Beatrice Richter Lebenslauf |date= |website=was-war-wann.de |language= de|accessdate=2014-11-17}}</ref>

She is the mother of actress Judith Richter (born 1978), who originates from a temporary relationship with the actor [[Heinz Baumann (actor)|Heinz Baumann]].<ref name="VKST" />

